Package: ggpubrplus
Type: Package
Title: 'ggplot2' Based Publication Ready Plots (Extended)
Version: 0.8.4.1
Date: 2026-02-05
Authors@R: c(
    person("Laszlo", "Erdey", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "erdey.laszlo@econ.unideb.hu",
           comment = "Faculty of Economics and Business, University of Debrecen, Hungary"))
Author: Laszlo Erdey [aut, cre] (Faculty of Economics and Business, University of Debrecen, Hungary)
Maintainer: Laszlo Erdey <erdey.laszlo@econ.unideb.hu>
Description: Supplementary compatibility updates for ggpubr (Kassambara, 2023),
    with flexible p-value formatting and modern R ecosystem support.
    Modern R ecosystem support (ggplot2 >= 3.5.2, dplyr >= 1.2.0, tidyr >= 1.3.2,
    R >= 4.1.0) - to be cited with the original package. The 'ggplot2' package is
    excellent and flexible for elegant data visualization in R. However the default
    generated plots requires some formatting before we can send them for publication.
    Furthermore, to customize a 'ggplot', the syntax is opaque and this raises the
    level of difficulty for researchers with no advanced R programming skills.
    'ggpubrplus' provides some easy-to-use functions for creating and customizing
    'ggplot2'-based publication ready plots. Features include customizable p-value
    formatting with predefined style presets (APA, AMA, NEJM, Lancet, GraphPad) for
    matching journal-specific publication requirements.
